                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-52">
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/52">John bar Aphtonia</persName> was named after his mother who consecrated him to God. 
                        He joined the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1464">monastery of St. Thomas in Seleucia</placeName>. He was later chased 
                        out of the area by Chalcedonians, and he founded the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/230">monastery of Qenneshrin</placeName> 
                        on the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/82">Euphrates</placeName>, across from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/83">Europos</placeName>. 
                        He wrote the Life of Severus of Antioch.
                    </note>
